Why CPCs so high? Increased 2.5x overnight

I'm sorry to hear about the sudden increase in your CPCs. There could be several reasons for this, such as changes in competition, targeting settings, or even recent updates to your campaign. Could you provide more details about any recent changes you've made to your campaign settings or if there were any specific events that might have influenced this change? This will help me assist you better.
CTRs are even better today as well. Other platforms reward for higher CTRs

Thanks for letting me know. If there haven't been any changes on your end, the increase in CPCs might be due to external factors like increased competition or seasonal trends. I recommend checking your campaign's performance over a longer period to identify any patterns or trends. Additionally, you can use the bid estimation tool in Newsbreak's Ad Manager to help project conversion, cost, and impression metrics based on different bid rates. If you need further assistance, feel free to reach out!

It's great to hear that your CTRs are improving! While higher CTRs are generally a positive indicator, CPCs can still be influenced by other factors like competition and market demand. On Newsbreak, it's important to consider the overall performance of your campaign, including conversion rates and ROI. You might want to explore optimizing your targeting or adjusting your bid strategy using the tools available in the Ad Manager. If you have any specific questions or need further guidance, feel free to ask!
